 Phase 2 — Query, Search, Graph & Daily Notes

 Goal: Query the index structurally, search by keyword (FTS5), export the graph, and manage daily notes.

 2.1 Query engine (core/query.rs, cli/query.rs)

 v1: Structured flags (composable, discoverable, shell-completable):
 oi query --tag rust                     # notes with tag #rust
 oi query --tag rust --tag async         # intersection (AND)
 oi query --link api-design              # notes that link to api-design
 oi query --backlink api-design          # notes linked FROM api-design
 oi query --title auth                   # title contains "auth"
 oi query --front "status=draft"         # frontmatter field match
 oi query --min-words 1000               # word count filter
 oi query --orphan                       # notes with no inbound or outbound links

 Internal design: all flags produce a composable Filter enum:
 enum Filter {
     Tag(String),
     Link(String),
     Backlink(String),
     Title(String),
     Frontmatter(String, String),
     MinWords(usize),
     MaxWords(usize),
     Orphan,
     And(Vec<Filter>),
     Or(Vec<Filter>),
     Not(Box<Filter>),
 }

 v1 uses AND for all flags. The Filter tree supports OR/NOT for a future DSL
 parser that produces the same type — no technical debt.

 Output: table (default), JSON (--json), or just paths (--paths)

 2.2 Keyword search (core/search.rs, cli/search.rs)

 oi search "error handling"             # FTS5 keyword search
 oi search "error handling" --limit 20  # limit results
 oi search "error handling" --paths     # just file paths

 - Uses SQLite FTS5 with BM25 ranking (built-in)
 - Returns: path, title, relevance score, snippet with highlighted matches
 - Zero API cost — entirely local
 - Distinct from oi ai search (semantic/vector search, Phase 3)

 2.3 Check command (cli/check.rs)

 oi check                    # run all checks
 oi check --orphans          # notes with no links in or out
 oi check --broken-links     # wikilinks pointing to non-existent notes
 oi check --ambiguous-links  # wikilinks with multiple resolution candidates
 oi check --dead-tags        # tags used only once
 - Queries the index for each check type
 - Outputs a report with file paths and line numbers
 - Exit code 1 if any issues found (useful in CI/pre-commit hooks)

 2.4 Graph export (core/graph.rs, cli/graph.rs)

 oi graph                    # full graph as JSON adjacency list
 oi graph --format dot       # Graphviz DOT format
 oi graph --format json      # JSON (default)
 oi graph --filter --tag project-x  # subgraph by tag
 oi graph --depth 2 --root "api-design"  # ego graph, 2 hops from root

 JSON output shape:
 {
   "nodes": [
     { "id": "api-design", "path": "notes/api-design.md", "tags": ["#arch"], "word_count": 450 }
   ],
   "edges": [
     { "source": "api-design", "target": "auth-middleware", "line": 23 }
   ]
 }

 DOT output for piping to dot -Tsvg -o graph.svg.

 2.5 Daily notes (cli/daily.rs)

 oi daily                    # create today's note, print path
 oi daily --yesterday
 oi daily --date 2026-03-25
 oi daily --template path/to/template.md
 - Creates {daily_folder}/{daily_format}.md if it doesn't exist
 - If a template is configured, copies template content into new daily note
 - Prints the path to stdout (so users can do: nvim $(oi daily), or $EDITOR $(oi daily))
