 Phase 3 — AI Integration Layer

 Goal: Pluggable AI backend with embedding-based semantic search, LLM-powered commands, streaming output, cost transparency, and retry resilience.

 IMPORTANT: AI features that use cloud providers (Claude, OpenAI) incur API costs.
 Only Ollama is fully local/free. The architecture must make this transparent.

 Cost flow:
 - oi ai index → sends note content to embedding API → cost per token
 - oi ai ask/summarize/draft/connect → sends query + context to LLM API → cost per request
 - oi ai search → local cosine similarity over stored vectors → FREE after initial embedding
 - oi search → local FTS5 → always FREE

 3.1 Provider traits (ai/provider.rs, ai/embedder.rs)

 Using native async traits (Rust 1.75+, no async_trait crate):

 pub trait LlmProvider: Send + Sync {
     async fn complete(&self, prompt: &str, system: Option<&str>) -> Result<String>;
     async fn stream(&self, prompt: &str, system: Option<&str>) -> Result<Box<dyn Stream<Item = Result<String>> + Send + Unpin>>;
     fn name(&self) -> &str;
 }

 pub trait Embedder: Send + Sync {
     async fn embed(&self, texts: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>>;
     fn dimension(&self) -> usize;
     fn model_name(&self) -> &str;
     fn cost_per_token(&self) -> Option<f64>;  // for cost estimation
 }

 3.2 Provider implementations (ai/providers/)

 Claude (claude.rs):
 - Uses reqwest to call https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages
 - Reads ANTHROPIC_API_KEY from env
 - Model configurable in config.toml (default: claude-sonnet-4-6)
 - Supports streaming via SSE (server-sent events)
 - For embeddings: delegate to OpenAI or Voyage AI (Claude has no native embedding API)

 OpenAI-compatible (openai.rs):
 - Calls /v1/chat/completions and /v1/embeddings
 - Reads OPENAI_API_KEY from env
 - base_url configurable (works with any OpenAI-compatible API)
 - Supports streaming via SSE

 Ollama (ollama.rs):
 - Calls local Ollama REST API (/api/generate, /api/embed)
 - Default URL http://localhost:11434, configurable
 - No API key needed — fully local, no cost
 - Supports streaming natively

 Provider factory:
 - Read ai.provider from config, return the right Box<dyn LlmProvider> + Box<dyn Embedder>
 - Validate provider/model combination on construction
 - Missing API key → clear error: "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY not set. Required for provider 'claude'."

 3.3 Cost estimation (ai/cost.rs)

 Before any API-calling operation, estimate and display cost:
 - Count tokens in all content to be sent (approximate: chars/4 for English)
 - Look up cost per token for the configured model
 - Display: "This will embed ~200k tokens across 142 notes. Estimated cost: ~$0.02 (text-embedding-3-small). Proceed? [y/N]"
 - Flag: --yes to skip confirmation
 - Flag: --dry-run to see cost estimate without executing
 - After operation: display actual usage if the API returns token counts

 oi ai metrics:
 - Show cumulative API usage stats (stored in SQLite)
 - Tokens sent, tokens received, estimated cost, by provider
 - Per-command breakdown

 3.4 Embedding indexer (ai/semantic.rs)

 oi ai index                 # embed all notes, store in SQLite
 oi ai index --force         # re-embed everything
 oi ai index --dry-run       # show cost estimate only

 - Chunk notes into ~500 token segments (split on headings or paragraphs)
 - Batch embed chunks (configurable batch size)
 - Retry with exponential backoff on rate limits (backoff crate)
 - Store in embeddings table: byte offsets + preview + vector blob
 - Incremental: skip notes whose content_hash hasn't changed

 Vector search (no external vector DB needed for v1):
 - Load relevant embeddings from SQLite
 - Compute cosine similarity in Rust (fast enough for <50k chunks)
 - Return top-K results
 - Future optimization: HNSW index via usearch crate if needed

 3.5 AI commands (ai/commands.rs, cli/ai.rs)

 # Semantic search over notes (uses stored embeddings — no LLM call)
 oi ai search "authentication patterns"
 # → Returns top 5 notes with relevance scores and excerpts

 # Ask a question, grounded in your notes (streams response)
 oi ai ask "What are our conventions for error handling?"
 # → LLM answers using retrieved note context (RAG), streamed to terminal

 # Suggest connections between a note and the rest of the vault
 oi ai connect api-design
 # → "api-design.md could link to: error-handling.md (both discuss middleware),
 #    auth-patterns.md (shared context on request lifecycle)"

 # Summarize a set of notes
 oi ai summarize --tag "#meeting-notes"
 # → Generates a summary across all matching notes

 # Generate a draft note from context
 oi ai draft "Compare our auth approaches" --context "#auth"
 # → Creates a new .md file with AI-generated content, linked to source notes

 All LLM-calling commands (ask, summarize, draft, connect):
 - Stream responses to terminal by default
 - Flag: --no-stream for batch mode (returns complete response)
 - Display source citations (which notes were used as context)

 RAG implementation (ai/context.rs):
 1. Embed the query → vector search → retrieve top-K chunks
 2. Load full chunk text from disk using byte offsets (not stored in DB)
 3. Assemble a prompt with the retrieved chunks as context
 4. System prompt instructs the LLM to only use provided context, cite sources
 5. Stream the response with source attribution

